# Gitea Provider

The Gitea provider allows Terraform to manage [Gitea](https://gitea.io/) resources such as users, organizations, repositories, teams, and more.

Use the navigation to the left to read about the available resources and data sources.

## Authentication

The provider requires administrator credentials to manage Gitea resources. Authentication can be configured using:

- **Provider Configuration Block**: Set credentials directly in the provider block
- **Environment Variables**: Use `GITEA_USERNAME`, `GITEA_PASSWORD`, and `GITEA_HOSTNAME`

~> **Important:** The authenticated user must have administrator privileges on the Gitea instance.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/provider/provider.tf"}}

### Using Environment Variables

```bash
export GITEA_USERNAME="admin"
export GITEA_PASSWORD="your-password"
export GITEA_HOSTNAME="https://gitea.example.com"
```

```terraform
terraform {
  required_providers {
    gitea = {
      source = "maxsargentdev/gitea"
    }
  }
}

provider "gitea" {
  # Configuration will be read from environment variables
}
```

### With Custom CA Certificate

```terraform
provider "gitea" {
  gitea_username = "admin"
  gitea_password = "your-password"
  gitea_hostname = "https://gitea.example.com"
  ca_cert_file   = "/path/to/ca-cert.pem"
}
```

### Skip TLS Verification (Not Recommended for Production)

```terraform
provider "gitea" {
  gitea_username      = "admin"
  gitea_password      = "your-password"
  gitea_hostname      = "https://gitea.example.com"
  insecure_skip_verify = true
}
```

